The paper deals with the problem of scheduling and control synthesis for multiple agents, which is a typical problem in the field of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The proposed algorithm involves path synthesis and control law design, which are common topics in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also considers the reward and cost of satisfying each task, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
